class Solution {
    public char repeatedCharacter(String s) {
        boolean[] seen = new boolean[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (seen[c - 'a']) {
                return c;
            }
            seen[c - 'a'] = true;
        }
        return ' ';
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, using a boolean array to track seen characters. It returns the first character that appears twice. The space complexity is O(1) because the size of the boolean array is constant (26). 
